About Inventory Aging Report

Inventory Aging Report or Stock Aging Report provides vital metrics on how quickly the companie's inventory is moving. 
It is a list of items on hand(stock) grouped based on the length of time in inventory.
It is useful to identify the slow moving stocks in the inventory as well as the costs involved in storing and maintaining the products until they are sold.
It can either be made in automated mode or manual mode.

How to use IAR(Inventory Aging Report)

If used in an effictive manner, aging report is an important indicator of the company's financail health.
It helps to anticipate potential cash flow issues and reduce the financial risks.
IAR helps focus more on the money invested, returns on the invested amount and oppurtuninty cost of holding too many items in the inventory.


